024/**
025 * A bi-directional mapping of non-unique objects to positions in an ordering (which this generates), and vice versa.
026 * This class is very similar to {@link Arrangement}, but is bag-like instead of set-like, allowing repeats of the same
027 * key with different positions in the ordering. Useful for various indirection techniques where you want to be able to
028 * retrieve a value in several ways, such as with  multiple MultiArrangements all sharing the same ordering but with
029 * different types for keys.
030 * <br>
031 * Originally, this started as a generic linked hash map with with a fast implementation, originally from fastutil as
032 * Object2IntLinkedOpenHashMap but modified to support indexed access. The code is extremely close to {@link OrderedMap},
033 * and like OrderedMap you can look up keys by index, but this is specialized to int values which it can automatically assign.
034 * <br>
035 * <p>Instances of this class use a hash table to represent a map. The table is filled up to a specified <em>load factor</em>, and then doubled in size to accommodate new entries. If the table is
036 * emptied below <em>one fourth</em> of the load factor, it is halved in size. However, halving is not performed when deleting entries from an iterator, as it would interfere with the iteration
037 * process.
038 * </p>
039 * <p>Note that {@link #clear()} does not modify the hash table size. Rather, a family of {@linkplain #trim() trimming methods} lets you control the size of the table; this is particularly useful if
040 * you reuse instances of this class.
041 * </p>
042 * <p>Iterators generated by this map will enumerate pairs in the same order in which they have been added to the map (addition of pairs whose key is already present in the set does not change the
043 * iteration order). Note that this order has nothing in common with the natural order of the keys. The order is kept by means of a int-specialized list, {@link IntVLA}, and is modifiable with this
044 * class' {@link #reorder(int...)} and {@link #shuffle(IRNG)} methods, among other tools.
045 * </p>
046 * <p>This class implements the interface of a sorted map, so to allow easy access of the iteration order: for instance, you can get the first key in iteration order with {@code firstKey()} without
047 * having to create an iterator; however, this class partially violates the {@link SortedMap} contract because all submap methods throw an exception and {@link #comparator()} returns always
048 * <code>null</code>.
049 * </p>
050 * <p>
051 * Additional methods, such as <code>getAndMoveToFirst()</code>, make it easy to use instances of this class as a cache (e.g., with LRU policy).
052 * </p>
053 * <br>
054 * Thank you, Sebastiano Vigna, for making FastUtil available to the public with such high quality.
055 * <br>
056 * See https://github.com/vigna/fastutil for the original library.
057 *
058 * @author Sebastiano Vigna (responsible for all the hard parts)
059 * @author Tommy Ettinger (mostly responsible for squashing several layers of parent classes into one monster class)
060 */

138    /**
139     * Creates a new MultiArrangement.
140     * <p>
141     * <p>The actual table size will be the least power of two greater than <code>expected</code>/<code>f</code>.
142     *
143     * @param expected the expected number of elements in the hash set.
144     * @param f        the load factor.
145     */
146
147    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
148    public MultiArrangement(final int expected, final float f) {
149        if (f <= 0 || f > 1)
150            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Load factor must be greater than 0 and smaller than or equal to 1");
151        if (expected < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The expected number of elements must be nonnegative");
152        this.f = f;
153        n = arraySize(expected, f);
154        mask = n - 1;
155        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
156        key = (K[]) new Object[n + 1];
157        value = new IntVLA[n + 1];
158        //link = new long[n + 1];
159        order = new IntVLA(expected);
160        hasher = CrossHash.defaultHasher;
161    }

181        this(a.size(), a.f, a.hasher);
182        ensureCapacity(a.size()); // The resulting map will be sized for
183        System.arraycopy(a.key, 0, key, 0, a.key.length);
184        System.arraycopy(a.value, 0, value, 0, a.value.length);
185        order.addAll(a.order);
186        containsNullKey = a.containsNullKey;
187    }

304    private int realSize() {
305        return containsNullKey ? size - 1 : size;
306    }
307    private void ensureCapacity(final int capacity) {
308        final int needed = arraySize(capacity, f);
309        if (needed > n)
310            rehash(needed);
311    }
312    private void tryCapacity(final long capacity) {
313        final int needed = (int) Math.min(
314                1 << 30,
315                Math.max(2, HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((long) Math.ceil(capacity
316                        / f))));
317        if (needed > n)
318            rehash(needed);
319    }
320    private int removeEntry(final int pos) {
321        final IntVLA oldValue = value[pos];
322        final int popped = oldValue.pop();
323        if(oldValue.size == 0) --size;
324        fixOrder(pos);
325        shiftKeys(pos);
326        fixValues();
327        if (oldValue.size == 0 && size < (maxFill >>> 2) && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
328            rehash(n / 2);
329        return popped;
330    }
331    private int removeNullEntry() {
332        containsNullKey = false;
333        key[n] = null;
334        final IntVLA oldValue = value[n];
335        final int popped = oldValue.pop();
336        if(oldValue.size == 0) --size;
337        fixOrder(n);
338        fixValues();
339        if (oldValue.size == 0 && size < (maxFill >>> 2) && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
340            rehash(n / 2);
341        return popped;
342    }

401    private int insert(final K k) {
402        return insertAt(k, order.size);
403    }
404    private int insertAt(final K k, final int at) {
405        int pos;
406        if (k == null) {
407            if (containsNullKey) {
408                value[n].add(at);
409                order.add(n);
410                return n;
411            }
412            containsNullKey = true;
413            pos = n;
414        } else {
415            K curr;
416            final K[] key = this.key;
417            // The starting point.
418            if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) != null) {
419                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
420                    value[pos].add(at);
421                    order.insert(at, pos);
422                    return pos;
423                }
424                while ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) != null)
425                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
426                        value[pos].add(at);
427                        order.insert(at, pos);
428                        return pos;
429                    }
430            }
431        }
432        key[pos] = k;
433        if (size == 0) {
434            first = last = pos;
435        } else {
436            last = pos;
437        }
438        order.insert(at, pos);
439        value[pos] = new IntVLA(8);
440        value[pos].add(at);
441        if (size++ >= maxFill)
442            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
443        return -1;
444    }
445
446    public int add(final K k) {
447        final int pos = insert(k);
448        if (pos < 0)
449            return defRetValue;
450        final IntVLA oldValue = value[pos];
451        oldValue.add(order.size - 1);
452        return order.size - 1;
453    }

463    protected void fixValues()
464    {
465        for (int i = 0; i < order.size; i++) {
466            value[order.items[i]].clear();
467        }
468        for (int i = 0; i < order.size; i++) {
469            value[order.items[i]].add(i);
470        }
471    }

473    /**
474     * Shifts left entries with the specified hash code, starting at the
475     * specified position, and empties the resulting free entry.
476     *
477     * @param pos
478     *            a starting position.
479     */
480    protected final void shiftKeys(int pos) {
481        // Shift entries with the same hash.
482        int last, slot;
483        K curr;
484        final K[] key = this.key;
485        for (;;) {
486            pos = ((last = pos) + 1) & mask;
487            for (;;) {
488                if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
489                    key[last] = null;
490                    return;
491                }
492                slot = (hasher.hash(curr))
493                        & mask;
494                if (last <= pos ? last >= slot || slot > pos : last >= slot
495                        && slot > pos)
496                    break;
497                pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
498            }
499            key[last] = curr;
500            fixOrder(pos, last);
501        }
502    }
503    /**
504     * Shifts left entries with the specified hash code, starting at the
505     * specified position, and empties the resulting free entry.
506     *
507     * @param pos
508     *            a starting position.
509     */
510    protected final void shiftKeysValues(int pos) {
511        // Shift entries with the same hash.
512        int last, slot;
513        K curr;
514        IntVLA v;
515        final K[] key = this.key;
516        final IntVLA[] val = this.value;
517        for (;;) {
518            pos = ((last = pos) + 1) & mask;
519            for (;;) {
520                if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
521                    key[last] = null;
522                    val[last] = null;
523                    return;
524                }
525                v = val[pos];
526                slot = (hasher.hash(curr))
527                        & mask;
528                if (last <= pos ? last >= slot || slot > pos : last >= slot
529                        && slot > pos)
530                    break;
531                pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
532            }
533            key[last] = curr;
534            val[last] = v;
535            fixOrder(pos, last);
536        }
537    }

539    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
540    protected int rem(final Object k) {
541        if (k == null) {
542            if (containsNullKey)
543                return removeNullEntry();
544            return defRetValue;
545        }
546        K curr;
547        final K[] key = this.key;
548        int pos;
549        // The starting point.
550        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
551            return defRetValue;
552        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
553            return removeEntry(pos);
554        while (true) {
555            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
556                return defRetValue;
557            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
558                return removeEntry(pos);
559        }
560    }
561    public int remove(Object o)
562    {
563        return rem(o);
564    }
565    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
566    public int removeInt(final Object k) {
567        if (k == null) {
568            if (containsNullKey)
569                return removeNullEntry();
570            return defRetValue;
571        }
572        K curr;
573        final K[] key = this.key;
574        int pos;
575        // The starting point.
576        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
577            return defRetValue;
578        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
579            return removeEntry(pos);
580        while (true) {
581            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
582                return defRetValue;
583            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
584                return removeEntry(pos);
585        }
586    }

611    private void moveIndexToFirst(final int i) {
612        if(order.size <= 1 || first == i)
613            return;
614        order.moveToFirst(i);
615        if (last == i) {
616            last = order.peek();
617            //last = (int) (link[i] >>> 32);
618            // Special case of SET_NEXT( link[ last ], -1 );
619            //link[last] |= -1 & 0xFFFFFFFFL;
620        }/* else {
621            final long linki = link[i];
622            final int prev = (int) (linki >>> 32);
623            final int next = (int) linki;
624            link[prev] ^= ((link[prev] ^ (linki & 0xFFFFFFFFL)) & 0xFFFFFFFFL);
625            link[next] ^= ((link[next] ^ (linki & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000L)) & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000L);
626        }
627        link[first] ^= ((link[first] ^ ((i & 0xFFFFFFFFL) << 32)) & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000L);
628        link[i] = ((-1 & 0xFFFFFFFFL) << 32) | (first & 0xFFFFFFFFL);
629        */
630        first = i;
631        fixValues();
632    }
633    private void moveIndexToLast(final int i) {
634        if(order.size <= 1 || last == i)
635            return;
636        order.moveToLast(i);
637        if (first == i) {
638            first = order.get(0);
639            //first = (int) link[i];
640            // Special case of SET_PREV( link[ first ], -1 );
641            //link[first] |= (-1 & 0xFFFFFFFFL) << 32;
642        } /*else {
643            final long linki = link[i];
644            final int prev = (int) (linki >>> 32);
645            final int next = (int) linki;
646            link[prev] ^= ((link[prev] ^ (linki & 0xFFFFFFFFL)) & 0xFFFFFFFFL);
647            link[next] ^= ((link[next] ^ (linki & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000L)) & 0xFFFFFFFF00000000L);
648        }
649        link[last] ^= ((link[last] ^ (i & 0xFFFFFFFFL)) & 0xFFFFFFFFL);
650        link[i] = ((last & 0xFFFFFFFFL) << 32) | (-1 & 0xFFFFFFFFL);
651        */
652        last = i;
653        fixValues();
654    }

656    /**
657     * Different from the typical get method; clears the non-null IntVLA, container, and fills it with any positions
658     * associated with k in this MultiArrangement. If you want to append to container instead of clearing it, use
659     * {@link #append(IntVLA, Object)}.
660     * @param container a non-null IntVLA; will be modified! Even if no entries are added, will be cleared
661     * @param k a K object or something that can be treated as one to search for
662     * @return the number of items added to container; 0 if none were added
663     */
664    public int get(final IntVLA container, final Object k) {
665        container.clear();

668    /**
669     * Different from the typical get method; adds to the non-null IntVLA, container, filling with any positions
670     * associated with k in this MultiArrangement. If you want a more convenient method for the case where you want
671     * container to hold only the items associated with k (discarding old contents), use {@link #get(IntVLA, Object)}.
672     * @param container a non-null IntVLA; will be modified unless nothing is associated with k
673     * @param k a K object or something that can be treated as one to search for
674     * @return the number of items added to container; 0 if none were added
675     */
676    public int append(final IntVLA container, final Object k) {
677        if (k == null)
678        {
679            if(containsNullKey) {
680                container.addAll(value[n]);
681                return value[n].size;
682            }
683            else
684                return 0;
685        }
686        K curr;
687        final K[] key = this.key;
688        int pos;
689        // The starting point.
690        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
691            return 0;
692        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr)) {
693            container.addAll(value[pos]);
694            return value[pos].size;
695        }
696        // There's always an unused entry.
697        while (true) {
698            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
699                return 0;
700            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
701            {
702                container.addAll(value[pos]);
703                return value[pos].size;
704            }
705        }
706    }

708    public boolean containsKey(final Object k) {
709        if (k == null)
710            return containsNullKey;
711        K curr;
712        final K[] key = this.key;
713        int pos;
714        // The starting point.
715        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
716            return false;
717        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
718            return true;
719        // There's always an unused entry.
720        while (true) {
721            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
722                return false;
723            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
724                return true;
725        }
726    }

995        public int nextEntry() {
996            if (!hasNext())
997                throw new NoSuchElementException();
998            curr = next;
999            if(++index >= order.size)
1000                next = -1;
1001            else
1002                next = order.get(index);//(int) link[curr];

1006        public int previousEntry() {
1007            if (!hasPrevious())
1008                throw new NoSuchElementException();
1009            curr = prev;
1010            if(--index < 1)
1011                prev = -1;
1012            else
1013                prev = order.get(index - 1);
1014            //prev = (int) (link[curr] >>> 32);
1015            next = curr;
1016            return curr;

1018        public void remove() {
1019            ensureIndexKnown();
1020            if (curr == -1)
1021                throw new IllegalStateException();
1022            if (curr == prev) {
1023                                /*
1024                                 * If the last operation was a next(), we are removing an entry
1025                                 * that precedes the current index, and thus we must decrement
1026                                 * it.
1027                                 */
1028                if(--index >= 1)
1029                    prev = order.get(index - 1); //(int) (link[curr] >>> 32);
1030                else
1031                    prev = -1;
1032            } else {
1033                if(index < order.size - 1)
1034                    next = order.get(index + 1);
1035                else
1036                    next = -1;
1037            }
1038            /*
1039                         * Now we manually fix the pointers. Because of our knowledge of
1040                         * next and prev, this is going to be faster than calling
1041                         * fixOrder().
1042                         */
1043            if (prev == -1)
1044                first = next;
1045            if (next == -1)
1046                last = prev;
1047            final IntVLA iv = value[order.removeIndex(index)];
1048            iv.removeValue(index);
1049            if(iv.size == 0)
1050                size--;
1051            int last, slot, pos = curr;
1052            curr = -1;
1053            if (pos == n) {
1054                containsNullKey = false;
1055                key[n] = null;
1056            } else {
1057                K curr;
1058                final K[] key = MultiArrangement.this.key;
1059                // We have to horribly duplicate the shiftKeys() code because we
1060                // need to update next/prev.
1061                for (;;) {
1062                    pos = ((last = pos) + 1) & mask;
1063                    for (;;) {
1064                        if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
1065                            key[last] = null;
1066                            fixValues();
1067                            return;
1068                        }
1069                        slot = (hasher.hash(curr)) & mask;
1070                        if (last <= pos
1071                                ? last >= slot || slot > pos
1072                                : last >= slot && slot > pos)
1073                            break;
1074                        pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
1075                    }
1076                    key[last] = curr;
1077                    if (next == pos)
1078                        next = last;
1079                    if (prev == pos)
1080                        prev = last;
1081                    fixOrder(pos, last);
1082                }
1083            }
1084        }

1086            int i = n;
1087            while (i-- != 0 && hasNext())
1088                nextEntry();
1089            return n - i - 1;
1090        }

1092            int i = n;
1093            while (i-- != 0 && hasPrevious())
1094                previousEntry();
1095            return n - i - 1;
1096        }

1395     * <P>This method rehashes the table to the smallest size satisfying the load factor. It can be used when the set will not be changed anymore, so to optimize access speed and size.
1396     * <p>
1397     * <P>If the table size is already the minimum possible, this method does nothing.
1398     *
1399     * @return true if there was enough memory to trim the map.
1400     * @see #trim(int)
1401     */
1402    public boolean trim() {
1403        final int l = arraySize(size, f);
1404        if (l >= n || size > maxFill(l, f)) return true;
1405        try {
1406            rehash(l);
1407        } catch (Exception cantDoIt) {
1408            return false;
1409        }
1410        return true;
1411    }

1413    /**
1414     * Rehashes this map if the table is too large.
1415     * <p>
1416     * <P>Let <var>N</var> be the smallest table size that can hold <code>max(n,{@link #size()})</code> entries, still satisfying the load factor. If the current table size is smaller than or equal to
1417     * <var>N</var>, this method does nothing. Otherwise, it rehashes this map in a table of size <var>N</var>.
1418     * <p>
1419     * <P>This method is useful when reusing maps. {@linkplain #clear() Clearing a map} leaves the table size untouched. If you are reusing a map many times, you can call this method with a typical
1420     * size to avoid keeping around a very large table just because of a few large transient maps.
1421     *
1422     * @param n the threshold for the trimming.
1423     * @return true if there was enough memory to trim the map.
1424     * @see #trim()
1425     */
1426    public boolean trim(final int n) {
1427        final int l = HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((int) Math.ceil(n / f));
1428        if (l >= n || size > maxFill(l, f)) return true;
1429        try {
1430            rehash(l);
1431        } catch (Exception cantDoIt) {
1432            return false;
1433        }
1434        return true;
1435    }

1437    /**
1438     * Rehashes the map.
1439     *
1440     * <P>
1441     * This method implements the basic rehashing strategy, and may be overriden
1442     * by subclasses implementing different rehashing strategies (e.g.,
1443     * disk-based rehashing). However, you should not override this method
1444     * unless you understand the internal workings of this class.
1445     *
1446     * @param newN
1447     *            the new size
1448     */
1449
1450    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
1451    protected void rehash(final int newN) {
1452        final K[] key = this.key;
1453        final IntVLA[] value = this.value;
1454        final int mask = newN - 1; // Note that this is used by the hashing macro
1455        final K[] newKey = (K[]) new Object[newN + 1];
1456        K k;
1457        final IntVLA[] newValue = new IntVLA[newN + 1];
1458        int i, pos, sz = order.size, originalFirst = first, originalLast = last;
1459        for (int q = 0; q < sz; q++) {
1460            i = order.get(q);
1461            if ((k = key[i]) == null)
1462                pos = newN;
1463            else {
1464                pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask;
1465                while (!(newKey[pos] == null))
1466                    pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
1467            }
1468            newKey[pos] = k;
1469            newValue[pos] = value[i];
1470            order.set(q, pos);
1471            if(i == originalFirst)
1472                first = pos;
1473            if(i == originalLast)
1474                last = pos;
1475        }
1476        n = newN;
1477        this.mask = mask;
1478        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
1479        this.key = newKey;
1480        this.value = newValue;
1481    }

1483     * Returns a deep copy of this map.
1484     *
1485     * <P>
1486     * This method performs a deep copy of this MultiArrangement; the data stored in the
1487     * map, however, is not cloned. Note that this makes a difference only for
1488     * object keys.
1489     *
1490     * @return a deep copy of this map.
1491     */
1492    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
1493    @GwtIncompatible
1494    public MultiArrangement<K> clone() {
1495        MultiArrangement<K> c;
1496        try {
1497            c = (MultiArrangement<K>) super.clone();
1498            c.key = (K[]) new Object[n + 1];
1499            System.arraycopy(key, 0, c.key, 0, n + 1);
1500            c.value = new IntVLA[n + 1];
1501            System.arraycopy(value, 0, c.value, 0, n + 1);
1502            c.order = (IntVLA) order.clone();
1503            c.hasher = hasher;
1504            return c;
1505        } catch (Exception cantHappen) {
1506            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(cantHappen + (cantHappen.getMessage() != null ?
1507                    "; " + cantHappen.getMessage() : ""));
1508        }
1509    }
1510    /**
1511     * Returns a hash code for this map.
1512     *
1513     * This method overrides the generic method provided by the superclass.
1514     * Since <code>equals()</code> is not overriden, it is important that the
1515     * value returned by this method is the same value as the one returned by
1516     * the overriden method.
1517     *
1518     * @return a hash code for this map.
1519     */
1520    public int hashCode() {
1521        int h = 0;
1522        for (int j = realSize(), i = 0, t = 0; j-- != 0;) {
1523            while (key[i] == null)
1524                i++;
1525            if (this != key[i])
1526                t = hasher.hash(key[i]);
1527            t ^= value[i].hashHive();
1528            h += t;
1529            i++;
1530        }
1531        // Zero / null keys have hash zero.
1532        if (containsNullKey)
1533            h += value[n].hashHive();
1534        return h;
1535    }

1540     * @param f the load factor.

1544        /* We must guarantee that there is always at least
1545                 * one free entry (even with pathological load factors). */
1546        return Math.min((int) Math.ceil(n * f), n - 1);

1563     * Returns the least power of two smaller than or equal to 2<sup>30</sup> and larger than or equal to <code>Math.ceil( expected / f )</code>.
1564     *
1565     * @param expected the expected number of elements in a hash table.
1566     * @param f        the load factor.
1567     * @return the minimum possible size for a backing array.
1568     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if the necessary size is larger than 2<sup>30</sup>.
1569     */

1571        final long s = Math.max(2, HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((long) Math.ceil(expected / f)));
1572        if (s > (1 << 30))
1573            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Too large (" + expected + " expected elements with load factor " + f + ")");
1574        return (int) s;

1578     * Unwraps an iterator into an array starting at a given offset for a given number of elements.
1579     * <p>
1580     * <P>This method iterates over the given type-specific iterator and stores the elements returned, up to a maximum of <code>length</code>, in the given array starting at <code>offset</code>. The
1581     * number of actually unwrapped elements is returned (it may be less than <code>max</code> if the iterator emits less than <code>max</code> elements).
1582     *
1583     * @param i      a type-specific iterator.
1584     * @param array  an array to contain the output of the iterator.
1585     * @param offset the first element of the array to be returned.
1586     * @param max    the maximum number of elements to unwrap.
1587     * @return the number of elements unwrapped.
1588     */
1589    private int unwrap(final ValueIterator i, final Object[] array, int offset, final int max) {
1590        if (max < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The maximum number of elements (" + max + ") is negative");
1591        if (offset < 0 || offset + max > array.length) throw new IllegalArgumentException();
1592        int j = max;
1593        while (j-- != 0 && i.hasNext())
1594            array[offset++] = i.next();
1595        return max - j - 1;
1596    }

1766    /**
1767     * Given an array or varargs of replacement indices for this MultiArrangement's iteration order, reorders this so the
1768     * first item in the returned version is the same as {@code getAt(ordering[0])} (with some care taken for negative
1769     * or too-large indices), the second item in the returned version is the same as {@code getAt(ordering[1])}, etc.
1770     * <br>
1771     * Negative indices are considered reversed distances from the end of ordering, so -1 refers to the same index as
1772     * {@code ordering[ordering.length - 1]}. If ordering is smaller than {@code size()}, only the indices up to the
1773     * length of ordering will be modified. If ordering is larger than {@code size()}, only as many indices will be
1774     * affected as {@code size()}, and reversed distances are measured from the end of this Map's entries instead of
1775     * the end of ordering. Duplicate values in ordering will produce duplicate values in the returned Map.
1776     * <br>
1777     * This method modifies this MultiArrangement in-place and also returns it for chaining.
1778     * @param ordering an array or varargs of int indices, where the nth item in ordering changes the nth item in this
1779     *                 Map to have the value currently in this Map at the index specified by the value in ordering
1780     * @return this for chaining, after modifying it in-place
1781     */
1782    public MultiArrangement<K> reorder(int... ordering)
1783    {
1784        if(ordering == null || ordering.length <= 0)
1785            return this;
1786        order.reorder(ordering);
1787        first = order.get(0);
1788        last = order.peek();
1789        fixValues();
1790        return this;

1792    private boolean alterEntry(final int pos, final K replacement) {
1793        final IntVLA[] value = this.value;
1794        final IntVLA v = value[pos];
1795        final int op = order.indexOf(pos);
1796        final boolean isFirst = op == 0, isLast = op == order.size - 1;
1797        shiftKeysValues(pos);
1798
1799        int rep;
1800        if (replacement == null) {
1801            if (containsNullKey)
1802            {
1803                value[n].addAll(v);
1804                return true;
1805            }
1806            rep = n;
1807            containsNullKey = true;
1808        } else {
1809            K curr;
1810            final K[] key = this.key;
1811
1812            // The starting point.
1813            if (!((curr = key[rep = (hasher.hash(replacement)) & mask]) == null)) {
1814                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1815                {
1816                    value[rep].addAll(v);
1817                    return true;
1818                }
1819                while ((curr = key[rep = (rep + 1) & mask]) != null)
1820                {
1821                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1822                    {
1823                        value[rep].addAll(v);
1824                        return true;
1825                    }
1826                }
1827            }
1828            key[rep] = replacement;
1829            value[rep] = v;
1830        }
1831        order.set(op, rep);
1832        if(isFirst)
1833            first = rep;
1834        if(isLast)
1835            last = rep;
1836        return false;
1837    }
1838    private boolean alterNullEntry(final K replacement) {
1839        containsNullKey = false;
1840        key[n] = null;
1841        final IntVLA[] value = this.value;
1842        final IntVLA v = value[n];
1843        value[n] = null;
1844
1845        int rep;
1846        if (replacement == null) {
1847            rep = n;
1848            containsNullKey = true;
1849        } else {
1850            K curr;
1851            final K[] key = this.key;
1852            // The starting point.
1853            if ((curr = key[rep = (hasher.hash(replacement)) & mask]) != null) {
1854                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1855                {
1856                    value[rep].addAll(v);
1857                    return true;
1858                }
1859                while ((curr = key[rep = (rep + 1) & mask]) != null)
1860                {
1861                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
1862                    {
1863                        value[rep].addAll(v);
1864                        return true;
1865                    }
1866                }
1867            }
1868            key[rep] = replacement;
1869            value[rep] = v;
1870        }
1871        fixOrder(n, rep);
1872        return false;
1873    }

1875    /**
1876     * Swaps a key, original, for another key, replacement, while keeping replacement at the same point in the iteration
1877     * order as original and keeping it associated with the same value (which also keeps its iteration index).
1878     * @param original the key to find and swap out
1879     * @param replacement the key to replace original with
1880     * @return the value associated with original before, and replacement now
1881     */
1882    public boolean alter(final K original, final K replacement) {
1883        if (original == null) {
1884            if (containsNullKey) {
1885                return alterNullEntry(replacement);
1886            }
1887            else
1888                return add(replacement) >= 0;
1889        }
1890        else if(hasher.areEqual(original, replacement))
1891            return false;
1892        K curr;
1893        final K[] key = this.key;
1894        int pos;
1895        // The starting point.
1896        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(original)) & mask]) == null)
1897            return add(replacement) >= 0;
1898        if (hasher.areEqual(original, curr))
1899            return alterEntry(pos, replacement);
1900        while (true) {
1901            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
1902                return add(replacement) >= 0;
1903            if (hasher.areEqual(original, curr))
1904                return alterEntry(pos, replacement);
1905        }
1906    }

1983    protected int positionOf(final Object k) {
1984        if (k == null)
1985        {
1986            return (containsNullKey) ? n : -1;
1987        }
1988        K curr;
1989        final K[] key = this.key;
1990        int pos;
1991        // The starting point.
1992        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
1993            return -1;
1994        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
1995            return pos;
1996        // There's always an unused entry.
1997        while (true) {
1998            if ((curr = key[pos = pos + 1 & mask]) == null)
1999                return -1;
2000            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
2001                return pos;
2002        }
2003    }

2005    /**
2006     * Swaps the positions in the ordering for the given items, if they are both present. Returns true if the ordering
2007     * changed as a result of this call, or false if it stayed the same (which can be because left or right was not
2008     * present, or because left and right are the same reference (so swapping would do nothing)).
2009     * @param left an item that should be present in this OrderedSet
2010     * @param right an item that should be present in this OrderedSet
2011     * @return true if this OrderedSet changed in ordering as a result of this call, or false otherwise
2012     */
2013    public boolean swap(final K left, final K right)
2014    {
2015        if(left == right) return false;
2016        int posL = positionOf(left), posR = positionOf(right);
2017        IntVLA l = value[posL];
2018        if(l == null) return false;
2019        IntVLA r = value[posR];
2020        if(r == null) return false;
2021        value[posR] = l;
2022        value[posL] = r;
2023        for (int i = 0; i < l.size; i++) {
2024            order.set(l.get(i), posR);
2025        }
2026        for (int i = 0; i < r.size; i++) {
2027            order.set(r.get(i), posL);
2028        }
2029        return true;
2030    }
2031    /**
2032     * Swaps the given indices in the ordering, if they are both ints between 0 and size. Returns true if the ordering
2033     * changed as a result of this call, or false if it stayed the same (which can be because left or right referred to
2034     * an out-of-bounds index, or because left and right are equal (so swapping would do nothing)).
2035     * @param left an index of an item in this OrderedSet, at least 0 and less than {@link #size()}
2036     * @param right an index of an item in this OrderedSet, at least 0 and less than {@link #size()}
2037     * @return true if this OrderedSet changed in ordering as a result of this call, or false otherwise
2038     */
2039    public boolean swapIndices(final int left, final int right)
2040    {
2041        if(left < 0 || right < 0 || left >= order.size || right >= order.size || left == right) return false;
2042        int posL = order.get(left), posR = order.get(right);
2043        value[posL].set(value[posL].indexOf(left), right);
2044        value[posR].set(value[posR].indexOf(right), left);
2045        order.swap(left, right);
2046        return true;
2047    }
